# n8n Workflows — Use Skill

When the task involves **investigating, debugging, or modifying n8n workflows** (or the user mentions n8n, webhooks, n8n nodes, workflow automation):

1. **Use the n8n-workflows skill** (`.cursor/skills/n8n-workflows/SKILL.md`). It contains the full playbook: hosting (n8n Cloud vs local), when to use n8n MCP first, template discovery, validation phases, batch operations, addConnection/IF-node syntax, and **run workflow before finalizing**.

2. **Do not** manually parse n8n export JSON when MCP is available; use MCP for current workflow state. Do not consider an n8n change done until at least one run completes successfully.

This rule ensures the agent pulls in the detailed procedure only when n8n work is actually needed.
